724638f-a.title: Manhattan: West Street - Vestry Street
724638f-a.text:
(1)
West Street, north from Vestry Street, showing foundation work
for the southward extension of the West Side Express Highway. Build-
ings seen on the right are Nos. 268 and 270-271 West Street, adjoining
and at the S.E. corner of Desbrosses Street.
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The samme, showing only the east side of the street, north to and
including Canal Street. It is at the latter point where this new
construction begins. For an account of same, see, the New York Times
of November 12, 1937.
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
